1]])\n*May 23, [[Kaoru Yosano]], politician (b. [[1938]])\n\n===June===\n*June 6, [[Keiichi Tahara]], photographer (b. [[1951]])\n*June 12, [[Masahide \u014cta]], academic, politician (b. [[1925]])\n*June 13, [[Y\u014dko Nogiwa]], actress (b. [[1936]])\n*June 22, [[Mao Kobayashi (actress)|Mao Kobayashi]], newscaster (b. [[1982]])\n*June 23, [[Nobuyuki \u014cuchi]], shogi player (b. [[1941]])\n*June 27, [[Ryoichi Jinnai]], businessman (b. [[1927]])\n*June 28, [[Shinji Mori]], baseball player (b. [[1974]])\n\n===July===\n*July 4, [[Masatoshi Yoshino]], geographer, climatologist (b. [[1928]])\n*July 8, [[Seiji Yokoyama]], musician (b. [[1935]])\n*July 11, [[Keisuke Sagawa]], actor (b. [[1937]])\n*July 18, [[Shigeaki Hinohara]], physician (b. [[1911]])\n*July 24, [[Michiko Inukai]], author, philanthropist (b. [[1921]])\n*July 25, [[Tar\u014d Kimura (politician)|Tar\u014d Kimura]], politician (b. [[1965]])\n\n===August===\n*August 1, [[Sh\u014dgor\u014d Nishimura]], film director (b. [[1930]])\n*August 3, [[Iwao \u014ctani]], recording engineer (b. [[1919]])\n*August 7, [[Haruo Nakajima]], actor (b. [[1929]])\n*August 18, [[Tadayoshi Nagashima]], politician (b. [[1951]])\n*August 28, [[Tsutomu Hata]], politician (b. [[1935]])\n*August 30, [[Sumiteru Taniguchi]], activist (b. [[1929]])\n\n===September===\n*September 7, [[Tsunenori Kawai]], politician (b. [[1937]])\n*September 8, [[Toshihiko Nakajima]], actor (b. [[1962]])\n*September 18, [[Kenji Watanabe]], swimmer (b. [[1969]])\n*September 25, [[Yoshitomo Tokugawa]], photographer (b. [[1950]])\n*September 29, [[Ry\u016bji Saikachi]], voice actor (b. [[1928]])\n\n===October===\n*October 4, [[Yosihiko H. Sinoto]], anthropologist (b. [[1924]])\n*October 11, [[Chikara Hashimoto]], baseball player (b. [[1933]])\n*October 16, [[Koichi Kishi]], politician (b. [[1940]])\n*October 18, [[Taizo Nishimuro]], businessman (b. [[1935]])\n\n===November===\n*November 16, [[Hiromi Tsuru]], voice actress (b. [[1960]])\n*November 21, [[Masao Sugiuchi]], go player (b. [[1920]])\n\n===December===\n*December 2, [[Norihiko Hashida]], musician (b. [[1945]])\n*December 8, [[Atsutoshi Nishida]], businessman (b. [[1943]])\n*December 9, [[Heitaro Nakajima]], engineer (b. [[1921]])\n*December 14, [[Tamio \u014cki]], voice actor (b. [[1928]])\n*December 15, [[Michiru Shimada]], screenwriter (b. [[1959]])\n*December 20, [[Kenichi Yamamoto (engineer)|Kenichi Yamamoto]], engineer and businessman (b. [[1922]])\n*December 21, [[Chu Ishikawa]], composer (b. [[1966]])\n*December 28, [[Junko Maya]], actress (b. [[1942]])\n*December 30\n**[[Tatsuro Toyoda]], businessman (b. [[1929]])\n**[[Sansho Shinsui]], actor (b. [[1947]])\n\n== Elections ==\n=== National ===\n* October 22: By-elections to the National Diet; 2 vacancies as of July 31, both from the House of Representatives: Ehime 3rd district and Aomori 4th district\n\n=== Prefectural ===\n* January 22: Yamagata gubernatorial (w/o vote)\n* January 29: Gifu gubernatorial\n* March 26: Chiba gubernatorial\n* April 9: Akita gubernatorial\n* June 25: Shizuoka gubernatorial\n* July 2: Tokyo legislative, Hy\u014dgo gubernatorial\n* August 27: Ibaraki gubernatorial<ref>[[Ibaraki Prefectural Government|Ibaraki prefectural electoral commission]]: [https://www.pref.ibaraki.jp/somu/shichoson/senkyo/senkan/2017chijisen.html Gubernatorial and assembly by-election 2017]</ref>\n* October 22: Miyagi gubernatorial<ref>[[Kahoku Shimp\u014d]], June 21, 2017: [http://www.kahoku.co.jp/tohokunews/201706/20170621_11005.html \uff1c\u5bae\u57ce\u77e5\u4e8b\u9078\uff1e10\u6708\uff15\u65e5\u544a\u793a\u300122\u65e5\u6295\u7968] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170816003540/http://www.kahoku.co.jp/tohokunews/201706/20170621_11005.html |date=2017-08-16 }}</ref>\n* November 12: Hiroshima gubernatorial<ref>[[Hiroshima Prefectural Government|Hiroshima prefectural electoral commission]]: [https://www.pref.hiroshima.lg.jp/site/sennkyokannriiinkai/29chijisentoukijitu.html Schedule of the 2017 gubernatorial election] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170730074149/https://www.pref.hiroshima.lg.jp/site/sennkyokannriiinkai/29chijisentoukijitu.html |date=2017-07-30 }}</ref>\n\n=== Major municipal ===\nElections in the 20 designated major cities and the 23 special wards/\"cities\":\n* January 29: [[Kitaky\u016bsh\u016b, Fukuoka]] legislative\n* February 5: [[Chiyoda, Tokyo]] mayoral\n* March 26: [[Shizuoka, Shizuoka]] legislative\n* April 23: [[Nagoya, Aichi]] mayoral\n* May 21: [[Saitama, Saitama]] mayoral<ref>Saitama city electoral commission, January 25 press release: [http://www.city.saitama.jp/006/009/008/p021070.html \u3055\u3044\u305f\u307e\u5e02\u9577\u9078\u6319\u306e\u9078\u6319\u671f\u65e5\u304c\u6c7a\u307e\u308a\u307e\u3057\u305f] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202062715/http://www.city.saitama.jp/006/009/008/p021070.html |date=2017-02-02 }}</ref> \n* May 28: [[Chiba, Chiba]] mayoral<ref>Chiba city electoral commission: [https://www.city.chiba.jp/senkyokanri/nittei.html Election schedules]</ref>\n* July 23: [[Sendai, Miyagi]] mayoral<ref>Sendai city electoral commission: [http://www.city.sendai.jp/senkyokanri-kanri/shise/senkyo/senkyo/yote.html Election schedules]</ref>\n* July 30: [[Yokohama, Kanagawa]] mayoral<ref>Yokohama city electoral commission: [http://www.city.yokohama.lg.jp/senkyo/what/shityousenkyokijitu.pdf 2017 mayoral election schedule] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325201924/http://www.city.yokohama.lg.jp/senkyo/what/shityousenkyokijitu.pdf |date=2017-03-25 }}</ref>\n* September 24: [[Sakai, Osaka]] mayoral<ref>Sakai city electoral commission: [http://www.city.sakai.lg.jp/shisei/senkyo/oshirase/senkyo_H290924.html 2017 mayoral and assembly by-election schedule] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085310/http://www.city.sakai.lg.jp/shisei/senkyo/oshirase/senkyo_H290924.html |date=2017-04-24 }}</ref>\n* October 1: [[Okayama, Okayama]] mayoral<ref>Okayama city electoral commission: [http://www.city.okayama.jp/senkyo/senkyo_00029.html Election schedules]</ref>\n* October 22: [[Kawasaki, Kanagawa]] mayoral,<ref>Kawasaki city electoral commission: [http://www.city.kawasaki.jp/910/page/0000087227.html 2017 mayoral and assembly by-election schedule] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170816011309/http://www.city.kawasaki.jp/910/page/0000087227.html |date=2017-08-16 }}</ref> [[K\u014dbe, Hy\u014dgo]] mayoral<ref>[[K\u014dbe Shimbun]], July 5, 2017: [https://www.kobe-np.co.jp/news/shakai/201707/0010343855.shtml \u795e\u6238\u5e02\u9577\u9078\u65e5\u7a0b\u6c7a\u307e\u308b\u3000\uff11\uff10\u6708\uff12\uff12\u65e5\u6295\u958b\u7968]</ref>\n* before December 18/November 12 (ends of term; but both elections were held on the same day in 2013): [[Katsushika, Tokyo]] mayoral and legislative<ref>Katsushika \"city\" electoral commission: [http://www.city.katsushika.lg.jp/information/1000080/1005822/1005831.html Elections] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171109110918/http://www.city.katsushika.lg.jp/information/1000080/1005822/1005831.html |date=2017-11-09 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Japan year nav}}\n{{Year in Asia|2017}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2017 In Japan}}\n[[Category:2017 in Asia|Japan]]\n[[Category:2017 in Japan| ]]\n[[Category:Years of the 21st century in Japan]]\n[[Category:2017 by country|Japan]]\n[[Category:2010s in Japan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Year in Japan|2017}}\nThe following is an overview of the year '''[[2017]] in [[Japan]]'''.\n\n==Incumbents==\n*[[Emperor of Japan|Emperor]]: [[Akihito]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Akihito {{!}} Biography, Reign, & Facts |url=https://www.britannica.com/biography/Akihito |website=Encyclopedia Britannica |accessdate=27 March 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Prime Minister of Japan|Prime Minister]]: [[Shinz\u014d Abe]]\n\n==Events==\n[[File:Hakimasue Asakura City 20170707.png|thumb|right|A debris flow caused by heavy rain in Asakura, Fukuoka Prefecture on 7 July 2017.